HTML
Importing React:        <script src="https://unpkg.com/react@16/umd/react.development.js"></script>
Importing React-DOM:    <script src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@16/umd/react-dom.development.js"></script>
Importing Babel:        <script src="https://unpkg.com/babel-standalone"></script>
Importing JSX:          <script src="first.js" type="text/jsx"></script>
Element where React should render:      <div id="root"></div>

To pass anything apart from strings in properties:
wrap in {} - for int, list, boolean, etc



Javascript:
Class for defining a component:
class Hello extends React.Component {
    render(){
        return (
            <div>
                <h1>Hello World!</h1>
            </div>
        )
    }
}

To render the component to DOM:
ReactDOM.render(<Hello/>, document.getElementById('root'))

To insert a Javascript Logic inside:
Wrap inside - {}                        Example: <h1>{12*16}</h1>